com.percussion.design.objectstore
Class PSField

java.lang.Object
  com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSComponent
      com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSField
All Implemented Interfaces:
IPSComponent, Serializable, Cloneable
public class PSField
extends PSComponent

Implementation for the PSXField DTD in BasicObjects.dtd. A field element contains all non UI related data required to define a field, including business rules. All DataLocator types except FieldRef are supported. If the DataLocator of a field specifies something other than PSXBackEndColumn, this field cannot be updated, it's for query only.

Field Detail

MODTYPE_NONE

public static final int MODTYPE_NONE
One of the possible values returned by getModificationType(). Means that this field is read only (computed) and is not persisted to the database. If the field was submitted, it would be ignored.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

MODTYPE_USER

public static final int MODTYPE_USER
One of the possible values returned by getModificationType(). Means that this field can be modified during an modification request by the submitter. This is the default.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

MODTYPE_USERCREATE

public static final int MODTYPE_USERCREATE
One of the possible values returned by getModificationType(). Means that this field can be modified by the user only when the item is submitted. It cannot be changed after that.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

MODTYPE_SYSTEM

public static final int MODTYPE_SYSTEM
One of the possible values returned by getModificationType(). Means that this field can only be modified by the server at any time. If the field was submitted, it would be ignored.

CLEANUP_PROPERTY

public static final String CLEANUP_PROPERTY
The property name used to save whether or not to cleanup this field before each insert/update. The only cleanup process currently supported is Tidy. The property is always locked and of type PSProperty.TYPE_STRING. Allowed values are specified in BOOLEAN_ENUM. Defaults to 'no'.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

CLEANUP_PROPERTIES_PROPERTY

public static final String CLEANUP_PROPERTIES_PROPERTY
The property name used to save the properties file used for the field cleanup process. The property is always locked and of type PSProperty.TYPE_STRING. The value of this property is a path relative to the Rhythmyx server root. The designer is responsible to make sure that the referenced file exists. Defaults to 'rxW2Ktidy.properties' available in every installation from the Rhythmyx root.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

DECLARED_NAMESPACES

public static final String DECLARED_NAMESPACES
A string property that lists the namespaces to declare on the field in text cleanup. These will be filtered in assembly to only include the namespaces that are actually defined for the site. If namespaces are included that are not defined for the system, i.e. have uris declared, then they will not be included.

a boolean property that tells text cleanup that JSP and ASP tags may appear in the content. These are escaped by inclosing them in processing instructions (PIs). These PIs have the name �psx-activetag�. The assembly system will selectively remove PIs from around these tags. It does this if the PIs name is �psx-activetag�. fixupDataType

public boolean fixupDataType(int jdbcType,
                             int precision,
                             int scale,
                             String typeName,
                             boolean searchEnabled)
Compares the current type against the supplied type. If the current type is not set, or is not storable in the supplied type, then the current type will be overwritten. The type is obtained via the getDataType() method. It also sets the search properties based on the type and the presence of an external search engine.

This method is public so it is accessible to classes outside this package, but it is not meant for general use.

Parameters:
jdbcType - One of the official JDBC data types found in SQL Types class.
precision - For numeric types, this is the number of significant digits in base 10, for char types, it is the size of the db column, in chars, for binary types, it is the number of bytes that can be stored in the db field. Set to -1 to indicate unknown.
scale - Only applicable to numeric types, it specifies how many decimal places the db colum has. Set to -1 to indicate unknown.
typeName - The db dependent name of the column for this type. May be null or empty. This is used when trying to determine if we can perform searches on this field.
searchEnabled - A flag that indicates whether the full text search engine is installed and enabled. This flag affects how the search properties are configured (which are dependent on the data type).
Returns:
true if the data type was changed, false otherwise.

merge

public PSField merge(PSField source)
              throws com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSValidationException
Gets shallow copy of this field merged with supplied source. The merged field will have all non-null properties of this field and overlays with properties of source for null properties of this field. Validates the following rules for merging.
  • If source has validation rules, target cannot also have them
  • If DataTypes are set on both, they must match. Otherwise, the set data type will be used in the merged field.
  • Occurence Dimension must match
  • ForceBinary must match
  • Locators must match if both have them
  • systemMandatory overrides are ignored

Parameters:
source - the source field to merge with, may not be null and must have the same name as this field.
Returns:
the merged field, never null
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if source is null or does not have same name as this field name.
PSValidationException - if the source or this field fails to meet one of the above rules.

demerge

public PSField demerge(PSField source)
Gets shallow copy of this field demerged with supplied source. The demerged field will have all properties of this field that differ from the properties of source and are allowed to be overriden. See merge(PSField) for details on what can be overriden.

Parameters:
source - the source field to demerge from, may not be null
Returns:
the demerged field, or null if nothing has been overriden.
